1
00:00:08,458 --> 00:00:09,958
♪

2
00:00:11,500 --> 00:00:14,041
[KIRIHITO]
These may be your friends now

3
00:00:14,125 --> 00:00:15,875
but in an instant,

4
00:00:15,958 --> 00:00:18,333
they could become
your greatest enemy.

5
00:00:19,833 --> 00:00:22,916
Moving speech, but let's see
if you can back up your talk,

6
00:00:23,916 --> 00:00:25,750
Onimaru Kunitsuna!

7
00:02:00,583 --> 00:02:03,125
[SAKI] Excuse me.
Is this the Odachi High tent?

8
00:02:03,208 --> 00:02:04,083
Uh...

9
00:02:05,208 --> 00:02:07,708
[REINA] Yeah, but the team's
already gone over to the ring.

10
00:02:07,791 --> 00:02:09,541
Oh, I missed them.

11
00:02:09,625 --> 00:02:11,916
You wouldn't happen to be
their manager by any chance?

12
00:02:13,041 --> 00:02:15,333
Huh? Who, me? No.

13
00:02:15,416 --> 00:02:17,458
I mean, it'd be normal
to have a female manager

14
00:02:17,541 --> 00:02:19,250
for a sport
like soccer or baseball,

15
00:02:19,333 --> 00:02:20,875
but sumo club, come on!

16
00:02:22,458 --> 00:02:25,666
I get it. In that case,
I must be abnormal.

17
00:02:25,750 --> 00:02:27,000
[REINA]
Uh...

18
00:02:27,083 --> 00:02:28,291
[ANNOUNCER]
Attention.

19
00:02:28,375 --> 00:02:30,666
The individual bouts
are about to begin.

20
00:02:30,750 --> 00:02:33,666
On the west side,
from Odachi High School, Ozeki.

21
00:02:33,750 --> 00:02:36,250
[OZEKI]
The individual tournament.

22
00:02:36,333 --> 00:02:39,708
Whoever makes it in the
top three goes to the finals.

23
00:02:39,791 --> 00:02:42,250
When this is over,
Ushio needs to make the podium.

24
00:02:43,291 --> 00:02:46,041
I was planning to sacrifice
my spot to help him out.

25
00:02:48,833 --> 00:02:50,833
But if I go deep
into the tournament,

26
00:02:50,916 --> 00:02:52,250
I might end up fighting him.

27
00:02:52,333 --> 00:02:53,750
Focus, Captain!

28
00:02:53,833 --> 00:02:55,958
-Uh...
-[REFEREE] Spirit!

29
00:02:56,041 --> 00:02:57,125
[grunts]
Oh, no!

30
00:02:57,208 --> 00:02:59,375
-I started too late!
-[yells]

31
00:02:59,458 --> 00:03:00,375
[REFEREE]
West side wins!

32
00:03:00,458 --> 00:03:02,875
[CROWD applauding]

33
00:03:02,958 --> 00:03:04,625
That was close.

34
00:03:04,708 --> 00:03:06,791
He almost got taken out.

35
00:03:06,875 --> 00:03:09,875
It's a good thing the other guy
got excited and moved too soon.

36
00:03:09,958 --> 00:03:11,625
Going off that match,
it's hard to believe

37
00:03:11,708 --> 00:03:14,125
he defeated the vice-captain
from Ishi High.

38
00:03:14,208 --> 00:03:15,500
[REINA]
Hmm.

39
00:03:15,583 --> 00:03:17,166
Seems like his drive to fight
is centered

40
00:03:17,250 --> 00:03:18,875
around helping his teammates.

41
00:03:18,958 --> 00:03:21,583
I got a feeling
he's nice to a fault.

42
00:03:21,666 --> 00:03:23,875
He was so concerned
with the group tournament,

43
00:03:23,958 --> 00:03:26,583
seems he lost sight
of the individual contest.

44
00:03:26,666 --> 00:03:28,958
-Huh.
-Well, whatever the case,

45
00:03:29,041 --> 00:03:30,375
you can't make it to the finals

46
00:03:30,458 --> 00:03:32,125
if you're unable
to face your friends.

47
00:03:32,208 --> 00:03:35,166
[ANNOUNCER] On the east side,
from Odachi High, Ushio.

48
00:03:37,416 --> 00:03:40,041
There's our champ!
No way Ushio can lose!

49
00:03:40,125 --> 00:03:43,208
Now that Sada's out, he's got
this in the bag for sure.

50
00:03:43,291 --> 00:03:46,791
I doubt he'll waltz through
this, given what happened.

51
00:03:46,875 --> 00:03:49,458
-You talking about his arm?
-That's part of it, yeah.

52
00:03:49,541 --> 00:03:51,458
But after making it
through today's gauntlet,

53
00:03:51,541 --> 00:03:53,333
can he stay focused
through more bouts?

54
00:03:53,416 --> 00:03:54,333
[REFEREE]
Spirit!

55
00:03:55,791 --> 00:03:56,750
[body thuds]

56
00:03:56,833 --> 00:03:58,750
[ALL gasp]

57
00:03:58,833 --> 00:04:02,541
♪

58
00:04:05,291 --> 00:04:07,708
It'd be a waste of time
to worry about him.

59
00:04:08,750 --> 00:04:10,416
[TERAHARA] He looks ready
to chew up and spit out

60
00:04:10,500 --> 00:04:12,625
anyone in his way,
teammate or not.

61
00:04:12,708 --> 00:04:14,083
[gasps]

62
00:04:14,166 --> 00:04:16,125
Do you guys think
when it's our turn,

63
00:04:16,208 --> 00:04:18,083
he's gonna fight
that way against us?

64
00:04:19,375 --> 00:04:22,083
It wasn't long ago
we were all working as one.

65
00:04:22,166 --> 00:04:24,125
Now it's like we're enemies.

66
00:04:26,166 --> 00:04:28,166
[CHIHIRO]
You don't stop being teammates.

67
00:04:28,250 --> 00:04:30,750
A little conflict
can be healthy.

68
00:04:30,833 --> 00:04:33,250
When you step inside the ring
to face off,

69
00:04:33,333 --> 00:04:36,166
it's against someone
who has a dream just like you.

70
00:04:36,250 --> 00:04:37,875
And they deserve
all that you've got

71
00:04:37,958 --> 00:04:39,500
'cause they're your teammates.

72
00:04:40,500 --> 00:04:43,125
If you want to call yourselves
sumo wrestlers,

73
00:04:43,208 --> 00:04:46,166
then shouldn't you demand
the same respect?

74
00:04:46,250 --> 00:04:48,791
I want to face him at his best.

75
00:04:48,875 --> 00:04:50,125
And win.

76
00:04:50,208 --> 00:04:53,625
♪

77
00:04:53,708 --> 00:04:54,750
[ANNOUNCER]
On the west side,

78
00:04:54,833 --> 00:04:57,125
from Odachi High School,
Kunisaki.

79
00:04:59,625 --> 00:05:00,583
[REFEREE]
Spirit!

80
00:05:01,875 --> 00:05:02,791
You're kidding me.

81
00:05:03,833 --> 00:05:05,416
Look at his footwork.

82
00:05:05,500 --> 00:05:06,625
That's Sada's.

83
00:05:06,708 --> 00:05:08,375
First Quarter Moon!

84
00:05:10,333 --> 00:05:11,625
-[grunts]
-[CROWD applauding]

85
00:05:11,708 --> 00:05:14,125
♪

86
00:05:14,208 --> 00:05:15,541
[BOTH gasp]

87
00:05:16,625 --> 00:05:17,791
That copycat!

88
00:05:17,875 --> 00:05:19,041
Hey, it's a good move.

89
00:05:20,125 --> 00:05:22,000
[KANAMORI]
I'd get copying the Demon Wheel,

90
00:05:22,083 --> 00:05:23,583
but this tournament
was the first time

91
00:05:23,666 --> 00:05:25,541
he's ever seen
the First Quarter Moon.

92
00:05:25,625 --> 00:05:27,041
♪

93
00:05:27,125 --> 00:05:29,750
[KIRIHITO]
He picks up on techniques fast,

94
00:05:29,833 --> 00:05:32,083
but his knack for combat
goes way beyond that.

95
00:05:33,291 --> 00:05:35,375
With Hinomaru
at his current state,

96
00:05:35,458 --> 00:05:36,583
there's a chance.

97
00:05:43,500 --> 00:05:45,250
I never thanked you.

98
00:05:45,333 --> 00:05:47,708
You're the reason
I joined the sumo club.

99
00:05:47,791 --> 00:05:50,416
Now I've grown stronger
than I've ever imagined.

100
00:05:52,125 --> 00:05:53,875
You're next on my list.

101
00:05:53,958 --> 00:05:57,166
A stepping stone to becoming
the world's strongest fighter.

102
00:05:59,208 --> 00:06:01,125
Yuma's bout is coming up next!

103
00:06:01,208 --> 00:06:02,500
Take him out!

104
00:06:02,583 --> 00:06:04,291
You got this, Yuma!

105
00:06:05,291 --> 00:06:07,166
[REFEREE]
Spirit!

106
00:06:07,250 --> 00:06:08,375
[ANNOUNCER]
Pushed out of bounds.

107
00:06:08,458 --> 00:06:10,166
-Nice!
-Gojo, on the west side, wins.

108
00:06:10,250 --> 00:06:12,166
Nice going out there, Gojo!

109
00:06:12,250 --> 00:06:13,666
[YUMA]
Thanks.

110
00:06:13,750 --> 00:06:15,750
I guess it's time, huh?

111
00:06:17,458 --> 00:06:20,541
On the east side,
from Odachi High, Ushio.

112
00:06:20,625 --> 00:06:23,416
On the west side,
from Odachi High, Kunisaki.

113
00:06:23,500 --> 00:06:25,250
♪

114
00:06:31,500 --> 00:06:34,125
Both of 'em are looking
dead serious.

115
00:06:34,208 --> 00:06:35,666
It makes you wonder.

116
00:06:35,750 --> 00:06:38,583
Just who are we supposed
to be cheering for?

117
00:06:38,666 --> 00:06:40,291
[OZEKI] I don't think
there's anyone on the team

118
00:06:40,375 --> 00:06:42,666
who can decide
which dream is worthier.

119
00:06:42,750 --> 00:06:44,875
Ushio or Kunisaki's.

120
00:06:46,083 --> 00:06:48,583
And if I keep winning my bouts,

121
00:06:48,666 --> 00:06:50,833
I'll end up fighting
whoever wins this one.

122
00:06:50,916 --> 00:06:52,750
Place your hands on the ground!

123
00:06:53,875 --> 00:06:56,041
[CHIHIRO]
He's a different beast entirely

124
00:06:56,125 --> 00:06:59,041
when you face him in the ring
for an official bout.

125
00:06:59,125 --> 00:07:01,291
Onimaru Kunitsuna,

126
00:07:01,375 --> 00:07:02,791
you're incredible.

127
00:07:07,291 --> 00:07:08,583
[REFEREE]
Spirit!

128
00:07:08,666 --> 00:07:10,250
Here we go!

129
00:07:11,458 --> 00:07:12,541
That's my move!

130
00:07:12,625 --> 00:07:15,041
The inner thigh counter!

131
00:07:15,125 --> 00:07:16,875
[KANAMORI]
The First Quarter Moon Throw.

132
00:07:16,958 --> 00:07:17,875
Now this.

133
00:07:17,958 --> 00:07:18,791
He's got talent.

134
00:07:18,875 --> 00:07:21,708
[grunting]

135
00:07:21,791 --> 00:07:22,833
[grunts]

136
00:07:23,875 --> 00:07:25,291
He threw an attack.

137
00:07:25,375 --> 00:07:27,541
Up until this point,
he's only been using grabs!

138
00:07:27,625 --> 00:07:29,500
There's no telling
what's gonna happen next!

139
00:07:29,583 --> 00:07:32,125
Think he modeled that move
off your Canon Slap?

140
00:07:32,208 --> 00:07:33,541
Mm-hmm.

141
00:07:33,625 --> 00:07:35,166
[SAKI]
He's definitely got an appetite

142
00:07:35,250 --> 00:07:37,166
for any moves
that'll help him win.

143
00:07:37,250 --> 00:07:40,375
And with so many talented
wrestlers at today's tournament,

144
00:07:40,458 --> 00:07:43,000
it's been like a buffet of
different powerhouse techniques

145
00:07:43,083 --> 00:07:44,083
for Kunisaki.

146
00:07:44,166 --> 00:07:46,041
[slaps landing]

147
00:07:46,125 --> 00:07:47,541
[KIRIHITO]
The way he absorbs moves

148
00:07:47,625 --> 00:07:49,416
and keeps changing his style,

149
00:07:49,500 --> 00:07:52,333
it's completely different
from the way he trains.

150
00:07:52,416 --> 00:07:53,416
But...

151
00:07:53,500 --> 00:07:55,958
you need more, Kunisaki.

152
00:07:56,041 --> 00:07:58,125
[OZEKI]
You won't beat Ushio like that!

153
00:07:58,208 --> 00:08:00,416
[KANAMORI] He isn't just
imitating the moves,

154
00:08:00,500 --> 00:08:02,875
so it's obvious he has skill.

155
00:08:02,958 --> 00:08:05,833
Even so, his versions don't have
the same intensity

156
00:08:05,916 --> 00:08:07,791
as the originals.

157
00:08:07,875 --> 00:08:11,083
You can tell because
Onimaru's body has barely moved.

158
00:08:12,083 --> 00:08:13,625
[OZEKI]
What would I do here?

159
00:08:13,708 --> 00:08:15,583
How'd I take advantage
of Ushio's stature

160
00:08:15,666 --> 00:08:18,541
without letting him grab
my mawashi belt?

161
00:08:18,625 --> 00:08:19,541
I'd try...

162
00:08:19,625 --> 00:08:20,916
-[thud]
-[ALL gasp]

163
00:08:22,791 --> 00:08:23,833
You thief!

164
00:08:23,916 --> 00:08:25,625
Whoa, Now he's using
a leg sweep?

165
00:08:25,708 --> 00:08:28,166
And not just any sweep!
That's Yuma's special!

166
00:08:28,250 --> 00:08:30,541
[CHIHIRO] All of these moves
have been a distraction

167
00:08:30,625 --> 00:08:32,458
to keep my options open.

168
00:08:32,541 --> 00:08:33,875
-My real attack...
-Uh!

169
00:08:34,875 --> 00:08:36,166
[CHIHIRO]
...is this!

170
00:08:36,250 --> 00:08:38,291
He's going for a tackle
from that position?

171
00:08:38,375 --> 00:08:40,791
[KIRIHITO] Kunisaki's strong
and has good technique,

172
00:08:40,875 --> 00:08:42,833
but his real weapon
is improvising.

173
00:08:46,958 --> 00:08:48,000
[CHIHIRO]
Damn.

174
00:08:48,083 --> 00:08:49,625
Looks like I'm not
the only one

175
00:08:49,708 --> 00:08:51,833
who got a power boost
during this tournament!

176
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:54,500
[HINOMARU]
Chihiro.

177
00:08:54,583 --> 00:08:58,000
I swear, every time
you exceed my expectations.

178
00:08:58,083 --> 00:08:59,958
[CHIHIRO] You're not getting
both hands on my belt!

179
00:09:00,041 --> 00:09:02,958
[HINOMARU] There's only one way
to counter your improvisation.

180
00:09:03,041 --> 00:09:04,458
I have to be stronger than you!

181
00:09:05,541 --> 00:09:08,291
Underarm throw,
thigh propping twist down!

182
00:09:08,375 --> 00:09:10,291
Demon Storm Hand Sweep!

183
00:09:10,375 --> 00:09:11,458
♪

184
00:09:11,541 --> 00:09:13,000
[whimpers]

185
00:09:14,458 --> 00:09:16,166
-[CROWD cheering]
-[KIRIHITO gasps]

186
00:09:16,250 --> 00:09:17,666
Not bad.

187
00:09:17,750 --> 00:09:19,291
How many techniques
does he have?

188
00:09:19,375 --> 00:09:20,541
Yeah, right?

189
00:09:20,625 --> 00:09:22,708
He saw Chiharu use it
in the team bouts

190
00:09:22,791 --> 00:09:24,166
and turned it against him.

191
00:09:25,250 --> 00:09:26,541
[CHIHIRO]
You know,

192
00:09:26,625 --> 00:09:29,416
the most annoying part is
even though I lost,

193
00:09:29,500 --> 00:09:32,208
I'm not the least bit
pissed off about it.

194
00:09:33,291 --> 00:09:36,083
To be honest,
I'm more stoked than anything.

195
00:09:36,166 --> 00:09:38,041
It means I've still got
a long way to go

196
00:09:38,125 --> 00:09:39,958
before I'm
the strongest fighter.

197
00:09:40,041 --> 00:09:43,416
♪

198
00:09:43,500 --> 00:09:45,416
[OZEKI]
Well, that gave me goosebumps.

199
00:09:45,500 --> 00:09:47,541
[SHIBAKIYAMA] If his mind wasn't
a mess already,

200
00:09:47,625 --> 00:09:48,875
it probably is now.

201
00:09:48,958 --> 00:09:49,916
Huh?

202
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:51,166
It's okay.

203
00:09:51,250 --> 00:09:52,875
You're a sumo wrestler too.

204
00:09:52,958 --> 00:09:55,583
You can respect him
outside the ring

205
00:09:55,666 --> 00:09:58,625
and still be able to compete
with him once you step inside.

206
00:09:58,708 --> 00:10:00,416
♪

207
00:10:00,500 --> 00:10:01,958
[OZEKI]
I want to fight Ushio.

208
00:10:03,375 --> 00:10:04,875
But that's not enough.

209
00:10:04,958 --> 00:10:06,875
I want to win!

210
00:10:06,958 --> 00:10:09,000
♪

211
00:10:10,458 --> 00:10:12,458
♪

212
00:10:14,916 --> 00:10:18,625
[groaning]

213
00:10:18,708 --> 00:10:21,083
[HINOMARU] Please don't give out
on me until this is over.

214
00:10:24,750 --> 00:10:26,000
[REFEREE]
Spirit!

215
00:10:27,875 --> 00:10:29,833
-He knew it was coming!
-It's over

216
00:10:29,916 --> 00:10:31,458
[KEI grunting]

217
00:10:33,416 --> 00:10:34,875
[CROWD applauding]

218
00:10:34,958 --> 00:10:37,625
Looks like his first
official win will have to wait.

219
00:10:37,708 --> 00:10:39,625
Nice fight, Mitsuhashi!

220
00:10:39,708 --> 00:10:42,916
[KEI] Damn. I wanted
to win at least one

221
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:45,000
before we headed to the finals.

222
00:10:45,083 --> 00:10:47,375
How can I win there
if I can't win in Chiba?

223
00:10:49,125 --> 00:10:51,333
Do you still have confidence
in my coaching?

224
00:10:53,166 --> 00:10:54,916
Have faith in me.

225
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:56,500
And I promise

226
00:10:56,583 --> 00:10:58,791
you'll win at the finals.

227
00:10:58,875 --> 00:11:00,791
[KEI]
You really have faith in me.

228
00:11:00,875 --> 00:11:02,291
You're our instructor

229
00:11:02,375 --> 00:11:04,500
and if you believe
I can actually win,

230
00:11:04,583 --> 00:11:06,375
then I will follow you.

231
00:11:06,458 --> 00:11:08,500
All the way to hell and back.

232
00:11:08,583 --> 00:11:10,583
[CROWD cheering]

233
00:11:12,125 --> 00:11:14,750
Whatever hang-ups
he might've had are gone now.

234
00:11:14,833 --> 00:11:16,125
Yeah.

235
00:11:16,208 --> 00:11:18,375
[KEI] Our captain put
his doubts behind him.

236
00:11:18,458 --> 00:11:21,291
I gotta catch up to the rest
of the team by the finals.

237
00:11:21,375 --> 00:11:22,958
West side wins!

238
00:11:23,041 --> 00:11:24,333
[CROWD applauding]

239
00:11:25,750 --> 00:11:27,208
[OZEKI]
There's no turning back.

240
00:11:29,958 --> 00:11:31,750
[ANNOUNCER] We're moving on
to the fifth bout

241
00:11:31,833 --> 00:11:33,500
of the individual tournament.

242
00:11:33,583 --> 00:11:36,541
On the west side,
from Odachi High School, Ozeki.

243
00:11:36,625 --> 00:11:39,541
On the east side,
from Odachi High school, Ushio.

244
00:11:39,625 --> 00:11:41,291
[MAN 1]
A bout between the captain

245
00:11:41,375 --> 00:11:43,041
and vice-captain
of the winning team?

246
00:11:43,125 --> 00:11:45,041
This is gonna be insane!

247
00:11:45,125 --> 00:11:47,708
So who're you cheering for,
Professor?

248
00:11:47,791 --> 00:11:49,750
-It's Hinomaru, right?
-Huh?

249
00:11:49,833 --> 00:11:51,333
Let's be real.

250
00:11:51,416 --> 00:11:54,208
You enrolled at Dachi High
to help him win, didn't you?

251
00:11:54,291 --> 00:11:57,083
So if the captain beats him,
then technically you failed.

252
00:11:58,083 --> 00:11:59,791
I won't deny you have a point.

253
00:11:59,875 --> 00:12:01,958
But as your coach,
I've watched you all shed blood,

254
00:12:02,041 --> 00:12:03,416
sweat, and tears equally.

255
00:12:03,500 --> 00:12:05,375
I wouldn't want the captain
to lose for the sake

256
00:12:05,458 --> 00:12:06,875
of someone else.

257
00:12:06,958 --> 00:12:07,833
However...

258
00:12:08,958 --> 00:12:10,791
I want you to tell everyone

259
00:12:10,875 --> 00:12:13,166
that my arm's
not as bad as it looks.

260
00:12:13,250 --> 00:12:14,541
[KIRIHITO]
What?

261
00:12:14,625 --> 00:12:16,458
I understand not wanting
other schools to know,

262
00:12:16,541 --> 00:12:18,708
but hiding it
from your own team?

263
00:12:18,791 --> 00:12:19,875
[HINOMARU]
Absolutely.

264
00:12:19,958 --> 00:12:21,166
[KIRIHITO]
Wha...

265
00:12:21,250 --> 00:12:22,375
[HINOMARU] You think
I'm gonna tell them

266
00:12:22,458 --> 00:12:24,125
to go easy on me
'cause my elbow hurts?

267
00:12:24,208 --> 00:12:25,833
[KIRIHITO]
That's not what I meant.

268
00:12:25,916 --> 00:12:27,250
Why risk making it worse,

269
00:12:27,333 --> 00:12:29,208
especially in a bout
with a teammate?

270
00:12:31,666 --> 00:12:33,583
-[HINOMARU] Respect.
-Huh?

271
00:12:33,666 --> 00:12:36,583
This tournament's important
to everyone here.

272
00:12:36,666 --> 00:12:38,583
I won't hold anything back.

273
00:12:38,666 --> 00:12:40,833
That's how I show respect
to my team.

274
00:12:40,916 --> 00:12:42,875
♪

275
00:12:46,875 --> 00:12:48,500
He never lets up.

276
00:12:48,583 --> 00:12:50,750
Even against the captain
of his own team.

277
00:12:50,833 --> 00:12:53,833
He kicked up the intensity,
if that's possible.

278
00:12:53,916 --> 00:12:54,750
Yeah.

279
00:12:54,833 --> 00:12:56,541
♪

280
00:12:59,125 --> 00:13:00,666
[OZEKI]
Ushio,

281
00:13:00,750 --> 00:13:02,708
I can never thank you enough
for what you've done for me.

282
00:13:03,958 --> 00:13:07,458
It's because of you, my love
for sumo has grown ten-fold.

283
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:10,375
You opened my eyes...

284
00:13:11,500 --> 00:13:13,375
to the joy
of having teammates...

285
00:13:14,916 --> 00:13:17,416
and winning against opponents.

286
00:13:17,500 --> 00:13:19,208
♪

287
00:13:21,583 --> 00:13:23,458
But those feelings
don't belong here.

288
00:13:24,500 --> 00:13:26,208
They're for outside the ring!

289
00:13:29,166 --> 00:13:30,625
[CHIHIRO]
A spider stance.

290
00:13:30,708 --> 00:13:33,500
How come he didn't use that
when we were fighting?

291
00:13:33,583 --> 00:13:34,875
Because you're unpredictable,

292
00:13:34,958 --> 00:13:37,166
so he wasn't sure
what you were going to do.

293
00:13:37,250 --> 00:13:38,625
But against Ozeki,

294
00:13:38,708 --> 00:13:40,500
he's expecting a tackle.

295
00:13:40,583 --> 00:13:41,833
[OZEKI]
This is the last Inter High

296
00:13:41,916 --> 00:13:43,000
I'm ever gonna have.

297
00:13:43,083 --> 00:13:44,750
Which means
this will be my first

298
00:13:44,833 --> 00:13:46,875
and only official bout
against Ushio!

299
00:13:46,958 --> 00:13:47,916
Spirit now!

300
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:49,500
Bring it!

301
00:13:49,583 --> 00:13:50,875
Holy...

302
00:13:50,958 --> 00:13:52,958
He stopped Onimaru's charge
with his chest!

303
00:13:53,041 --> 00:13:54,666
♪

304
00:13:54,750 --> 00:13:57,416
[OZEKI] I've dealt with this
every day of practice!

305
00:13:57,500 --> 00:13:58,500
You gotta do better!

306
00:13:58,583 --> 00:13:59,958
An underarm grip!

307
00:14:00,041 --> 00:14:02,208
Neither of his hands
can reach the mawashi belt!

308
00:14:03,208 --> 00:14:04,750
Hinomaru grabbed him back!

309
00:14:04,833 --> 00:14:07,583
[OZEKI] His grip isn't
as strong as usual.

310
00:14:07,666 --> 00:14:09,541
I'm guessing his arm
must've gotten busted up

311
00:14:09,625 --> 00:14:11,666
more than I originally thought.

312
00:14:11,750 --> 00:14:12,666
[groans]

313
00:14:12,750 --> 00:14:14,416
[BOTH straining]

314
00:14:14,500 --> 00:14:17,500
[OZEKI] If we continue fighting
like this, his arm's gonna...

315
00:14:18,500 --> 00:14:19,583
[HINOMARU]
What's wrong, Captain?

316
00:14:19,666 --> 00:14:21,291
Thinking of going easy on me?

317
00:14:21,375 --> 00:14:24,583
I'm warning you, if you do that,
we'll both be disappointed!

318
00:14:24,666 --> 00:14:26,583
[HINOMARU straining]

319
00:14:26,666 --> 00:14:28,625
He pushed him all the way
to the rope!

320
00:14:28,708 --> 00:14:30,250
Act like this is your last bout!

321
00:14:31,916 --> 00:14:33,416
That's right.

322
00:14:33,500 --> 00:14:35,875
For Shinya Ozeki, there's never
gonna be another match

323
00:14:35,958 --> 00:14:38,375
as important as the one
I'm fighting right now!

324
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:42,375
For me, this is the final!

325
00:14:42,458 --> 00:14:43,875
My main event!

326
00:14:45,666 --> 00:14:47,083
He pushed him backwards!

327
00:14:47,166 --> 00:14:49,583
[REINA] Now shorty's about
to get knocked out!

328
00:14:52,666 --> 00:14:54,375
[OZEKI]
He's pulling me down!

329
00:14:54,458 --> 00:14:56,000
I won't let him!

330
00:14:56,083 --> 00:14:57,458
Wait. A trap!

331
00:14:57,541 --> 00:14:58,708
He switched to underarm!

332
00:14:58,791 --> 00:14:59,958
[OZEKI]
Not today!

333
00:15:00,041 --> 00:15:02,250
He's not thrusting
with his right arm.

334
00:15:02,333 --> 00:15:05,000
Looks like Onimaru
injured it as well.

335
00:15:05,083 --> 00:15:07,250
You knew his arm was screwed up.

336
00:15:07,333 --> 00:15:09,875
So why didn't you say
anything, Prof?

337
00:15:09,958 --> 00:15:11,375
If you had known,

338
00:15:11,458 --> 00:15:13,916
would you have approached
the bout any differently?

339
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:14,958
You wanna know?

340
00:15:15,041 --> 00:15:16,291
Just look at the captain.

341
00:15:17,291 --> 00:15:19,041
[yelling]

342
00:15:19,125 --> 00:15:20,875
This is getting intense.

343
00:15:20,958 --> 00:15:22,791
It's like he's
a different person.

344
00:15:22,875 --> 00:15:24,583
[HINOMARU grunts]

345
00:15:26,333 --> 00:15:28,166
[CHIHIRO] The upper body
and cardio workouts

346
00:15:28,250 --> 00:15:29,416
the professor puts us through

347
00:15:29,500 --> 00:15:31,708
took our game
to a whole new level.

348
00:15:31,791 --> 00:15:33,875
But paired with the captain's
lower body strength,

349
00:15:33,958 --> 00:15:35,875
it's made him
a fearsome opponent.

350
00:15:35,958 --> 00:15:37,000
-[slap lands]
-[CHIHIRO] Still.

351
00:15:37,083 --> 00:15:38,625
-[yells]
-[grunts]

352
00:15:38,708 --> 00:15:40,125
[ALL gasp]

353
00:15:40,208 --> 00:15:41,625
[CHIHIRO] You really think
Hinomaru will let you win

354
00:15:41,708 --> 00:15:42,916
just cause he's injured?

355
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:43,833
Yeah, right.

356
00:15:45,208 --> 00:15:47,333
[OZEKI]
What do you think you're doing?

357
00:15:47,416 --> 00:15:49,250
You're using your busted arm!

358
00:15:50,375 --> 00:15:53,500
[HINOMARU] I can't complain
about this kind of pain.

359
00:15:53,583 --> 00:15:55,708
Especially when
I'm battling you.

360
00:15:56,833 --> 00:15:59,291
I had to fight alone
in middle school.

361
00:15:59,375 --> 00:16:02,208
Against both myself and society.

362
00:16:02,291 --> 00:16:05,750
I didn't accept any help,
or anyone's advice.

363
00:16:06,875 --> 00:16:08,291
I thought no one
could understand

364
00:16:08,375 --> 00:16:10,041
what I was going through,

365
00:16:10,125 --> 00:16:11,791
and I was fine with that.

366
00:16:11,875 --> 00:16:15,041
Until I saw that
homemade sumo ring.

367
00:16:15,125 --> 00:16:16,541
Up until that point,

368
00:16:16,625 --> 00:16:18,583
I refused to believe
there was someone out there

369
00:16:18,666 --> 00:16:20,625
practicing in harsher conditions
than me.

370
00:16:21,750 --> 00:16:23,333
For the first time in my life,

371
00:16:23,416 --> 00:16:25,333
I felt like I had
a brother-in-arms.

372
00:16:25,416 --> 00:16:26,708
[BOTH straining]

373
00:16:26,791 --> 00:16:28,250
My elbow's killing me.

374
00:16:28,333 --> 00:16:29,666
But so what?

375
00:16:29,750 --> 00:16:31,416
I'm not going to give
my captain anything

376
00:16:31,500 --> 00:16:33,583
except the best match
he's ever fought!

377
00:16:35,333 --> 00:16:36,750
Demon Wheel!

378
00:16:36,833 --> 00:16:39,166
♪

379
00:16:39,250 --> 00:16:42,625
[OZEKI] Ushio's laying it all
on the line to win this fight.

380
00:16:42,708 --> 00:16:43,958
Then why?

381
00:16:45,708 --> 00:16:46,791
[straining]

382
00:16:46,875 --> 00:16:48,875
Why haven't I
been doing the same?

383
00:16:48,958 --> 00:16:50,916
[ALL gasp]

384
00:16:52,458 --> 00:16:53,916
[OZEKI]
I can take it!

385
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:56,416
If this is battle of endurance,
I won't lose to him!

386
00:16:56,500 --> 00:16:57,666
[straining]

387
00:16:57,750 --> 00:16:59,916
[HINOMARU]
That's the spirit, Captain!

388
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:03,375
I don't see you any different
than Kuze or Sada.

389
00:17:03,458 --> 00:17:06,708
Right now, you're my rival,
pure and simple!

390
00:17:08,083 --> 00:17:09,250
[HINOMARU yells]

391
00:17:09,333 --> 00:17:11,541
[OZEKI]
Your grip's not tight enough!

392
00:17:11,625 --> 00:17:12,833
Hinomaru!

393
00:17:15,541 --> 00:17:16,833
Uh-oh.

394
00:17:16,916 --> 00:17:19,166
He's only gripping one layer
of the mawashi.

395
00:17:19,250 --> 00:17:21,500
That'll make it harder
for him to apply force.

396
00:17:23,250 --> 00:17:25,666
[BOTH grunting]

397
00:17:27,250 --> 00:17:30,958
He's standing his ground
and trying to push Ozeki out.

398
00:17:32,166 --> 00:17:34,083
[SADA]
If he could manage a throw,

399
00:17:34,166 --> 00:17:36,291
he'd be in
a much better position.

400
00:17:36,375 --> 00:17:38,000
That's what I'd do anyway.

401
00:17:38,083 --> 00:17:38,958
[chuckles]

402
00:17:40,083 --> 00:17:43,125
But backing off
isn't exactly Ushio's style.

403
00:17:45,083 --> 00:17:47,166
Ozeki's standing up straighter.

404
00:17:47,250 --> 00:17:49,791
That half-pint had
that much energy left to burn?

405
00:17:49,875 --> 00:17:53,250
[OZEKI] He's going full power
and not holding anything back.

406
00:17:53,333 --> 00:17:55,000
Which means
he's planning on using

407
00:17:55,083 --> 00:17:56,708
everything he's got right here!

408
00:17:56,791 --> 00:17:58,166
If I survive this,

409
00:17:58,250 --> 00:17:59,916
he won't have any strength
left in him to fight!

410
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:01,916
[inhales deeply]

411
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:03,458
Endure it!

412
00:18:03,541 --> 00:18:06,875
All I have to do is get
through this, and I'll win!

413
00:18:07,916 --> 00:18:09,583
Um, sir.

414
00:18:09,666 --> 00:18:12,125
I know this sounds crazy,
and maybe it's just me.

415
00:18:13,125 --> 00:18:15,208
But it seems like
they're both having fun.

416
00:18:17,000 --> 00:18:19,083
They are.
I can see it too.

417
00:18:19,166 --> 00:18:21,333
When it comes to their strength,

418
00:18:21,416 --> 00:18:23,166
they have a mutual admiration.

419
00:18:25,250 --> 00:18:26,875
I'm a little envious.

420
00:18:26,958 --> 00:18:29,333
What I wouldn't give
to have fought Hinomaru

421
00:18:29,416 --> 00:18:31,833
head-to-head
in a serious bout like this.

422
00:18:33,041 --> 00:18:34,333
[MAN] No matter
which of you wins,

423
00:18:34,416 --> 00:18:35,875
this bout is legendary!

424
00:18:35,958 --> 00:18:37,333
[MAN 2]
You're almost there, Ozeki!

425
00:18:37,416 --> 00:18:39,333
♪

426
00:18:39,416 --> 00:18:42,166
I keep forgetting
I have to breathe.

427
00:18:42,250 --> 00:18:43,875
Both of you, tough it out.

428
00:18:43,958 --> 00:18:44,833
[BATO scoffs]

429
00:18:44,916 --> 00:18:48,833
♪

430
00:18:48,916 --> 00:18:50,458
[grunting]

431
00:18:50,541 --> 00:18:52,250
[growling]

432
00:18:54,291 --> 00:18:55,708
[ALL gasp]

433
00:18:55,791 --> 00:18:57,208
[BOTH gasp]

434
00:18:57,291 --> 00:18:59,208
♪

435
00:18:59,291 --> 00:19:00,750
[ALL gasp]

436
00:19:02,041 --> 00:19:03,750
[straining]

437
00:19:08,291 --> 00:19:09,375
Ah!

438
00:19:10,916 --> 00:19:12,375
[ALL gasp]

439
00:19:15,333 --> 00:19:16,791
[body thuds]

440
00:19:16,875 --> 00:19:20,166
To everyone else, the ring
is just a rice-straw bale.

441
00:19:20,250 --> 00:19:22,208
-But for sumo wrestlers...
-[panting]

442
00:19:22,291 --> 00:19:24,541
...it's the size
of a fearsome mountain.

443
00:19:25,583 --> 00:19:26,833
[ANNOUNCER]
Forced out of bounds.

444
00:19:26,916 --> 00:19:29,083
Ushio, on the east side, wins.

445
00:19:29,166 --> 00:19:31,125
[cheering]

446
00:19:37,583 --> 00:19:40,083
Don't tell me that wasn't
an impressive battle.

447
00:19:40,166 --> 00:19:42,458
Ozeki held his own admirably,

448
00:19:42,541 --> 00:19:45,625
but in the end,
Onimaru's tenacity won out.

449
00:19:45,708 --> 00:19:48,750
You know, you'll likely meet
in the final bout.

450
00:19:48,833 --> 00:19:50,375
You scared?

451
00:19:50,458 --> 00:19:51,458
Please.

452
00:19:51,541 --> 00:19:52,958
Aww, man.

453
00:19:53,041 --> 00:19:55,666
I wish my arm hadn't decided
to give out on me.

454
00:19:57,041 --> 00:19:58,666
You better heal up quick.

455
00:19:58,750 --> 00:20:00,541
I need to train ASAP.

456
00:20:00,625 --> 00:20:03,000
Sada actually wants to train?

457
00:20:03,083 --> 00:20:05,541
After the match we just watched,
I can see why.

458
00:20:05,625 --> 00:20:08,583
[HINOMARU panting]

459
00:20:08,666 --> 00:20:10,125
[OZEKI]
Man, I'm disappointed.

460
00:20:11,375 --> 00:20:13,000
I wanted to win.

461
00:20:13,083 --> 00:20:14,916
But in terms
of matches I've fought,

462
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:17,375
it was the best I ever had

463
00:20:17,458 --> 00:20:20,416
and just the motivation I needed
to push me during the finals.

464
00:20:21,541 --> 00:20:24,375
There's gonna be a ton of strong
opponents standing in your way,

465
00:20:24,458 --> 00:20:25,875
but I know
you're gonna beat them all

466
00:20:25,958 --> 00:20:27,750
and become
a high school yokozuna!

467
00:20:27,833 --> 00:20:29,416
Correction.

468
00:20:29,500 --> 00:20:32,500
Everybody knows you're going
to be a professional yokozuna!

469
00:20:32,583 --> 00:20:33,958
[chuckles]

470
00:20:34,041 --> 00:20:36,500
-Wait, what have I done?
-[HINOMARU] Huh?

471
00:20:36,583 --> 00:20:38,083
Dude! Is your arm okay?

472
00:20:38,166 --> 00:20:40,000
I got caught up in the moment
and completely forgot

473
00:20:40,083 --> 00:20:41,791
about it getting
injured earlier!

474
00:20:41,875 --> 00:20:43,375
[laughing]

475
00:20:43,458 --> 00:20:44,916
As soon as he steps
out of the ring,

476
00:20:45,000 --> 00:20:46,750
he's back to being a teddy bear.

477
00:20:46,833 --> 00:20:49,166
[KIRIHITO]
Good luck, Hinomaru.

478
00:20:49,250 --> 00:20:50,750
♪

479
00:20:50,833 --> 00:20:53,375
[ANNOUNCER] We will now present
the tournament awards!

480
00:20:55,458 --> 00:20:57,833
The champion,
from Odachi High School,

481
00:20:57,916 --> 00:20:59,875
is Hinomaru Ushio.

482
00:20:59,958 --> 00:21:01,291
In second place,

483
00:21:01,375 --> 00:21:03,750
from Ishigami High School,
Kanamori.

484
00:21:03,833 --> 00:21:04,958
In third place...

485
00:21:05,041 --> 00:21:06,916
Congratulations, Ushio.

486
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:08,666
I'll be seeing you
at the finals.

487
00:21:09,666 --> 00:21:10,583
[BATO scoffs]

488
00:21:12,333 --> 00:21:14,541
Okay, everyone get close!

489
00:21:15,625 --> 00:21:17,583
[KIRIHITO] Hinomaru,
I know this was just

490
00:21:17,666 --> 00:21:19,000
a stop on the road for you,

491
00:21:19,083 --> 00:21:21,333
but you can still
look happy about it.

492
00:21:21,416 --> 00:21:23,041
Wha... I am.

493
00:21:23,125 --> 00:21:25,208
[REINA]
Come on, guys. Smile!

494
00:21:25,291 --> 00:21:26,625
-You too, shorty.
-Uh...

495
00:21:26,708 --> 00:21:29,125
♪

496
00:21:29,208 --> 00:21:30,375
[chuckles]

497
00:21:31,833 --> 00:21:33,541
-[REINA] Say cheese!
-[camera shutter clicks]

498
00:21:33,625 --> 00:21:37,916
♪

499
00:23:08,541 --> 00:23:10,083
Interesting.

500
00:23:10,166 --> 00:23:11,916
If they're holding the belt,
it's "forced out of bounds."

501
00:23:12,000 --> 00:23:14,458
Thanks for clearing
that up for me!

502
00:23:14,541 --> 00:23:17,708
I'm still a novice and don't
know a whole lot about sumo yet.

503
00:23:17,791 --> 00:23:19,708
Plus the guys who tagged along
were no help,

504
00:23:19,791 --> 00:23:21,833
so it's a relief
someone here's knowledgeable!

505
00:23:21,916 --> 00:23:23,208
No problem!

506
00:23:23,291 --> 00:23:25,500
I'm just happy you enjoyed
the tournament.

507
00:23:25,583 --> 00:23:27,208
Hey. If you wanna
check it out,

508
00:23:27,291 --> 00:23:29,333
I recorded Yuma's bout
on my phone earlier!

509
00:23:29,416 --> 00:23:31,000
[REINA on phone]
Whoo! Go, Yuma!

510
00:23:31,083 --> 00:23:32,291
Wipe the floor with him!

511
